<Author>lolaborro
<Content>A very good choice The best thing of this apart / hotel is its location. It is just off, Diego de Leon, one of the prime streets in Madrid. A very safe central location full of restaurants bars supermarkets and shops. It is also very close to a tube stop with access to lines 6 and 4.The appartments are well appointed. They are spacious and nicely furnished. I went for the smallest one and it had two large single beds, a desk, a small dining table wih two chairs and a sofa. The kitchen is well equiped but I've seen better. One of the main problems with the kitchen is that they don't provide washing up services, but they don't supply washing up liquid or a sponge to wash the dishes with or a space or cloth to dry them either so you have to either live with the dirty dishes or buy those items yourself, which is not always convenient.The bathroom suite are new and modern although my bed was a bit squeeky and the taps in the bathroom could do with a change.I've read previous comments about their reception staff. I found them to be fairly pleasant, nobody was rude to me, although I'm a local so maybe I'm a bit better at understanding the local culture. People in Madrid can be a bit arrogant some times, but it's not a particularity of QuoEraso's reception staff but rather a Madrid people's trait.The area is very quiet but the hotel isn't. There is this background music being placed in all corridors and you can hear it from the rooms. Very annoying. Another thing to take into consideration is that this type of place is often used by families with young babies because of the kitchen facilies, and children are loud, so be prepared to be woken up in the middle of the night by some screaming baby or to have the children in the room upstaris running up and down at 7 in the morning.The only thing that quite annoyed me about this place was the cost of making a phone call: 4.70 Euros for 3 minutes!!! use your mobile, even if you are on roaming, it's likely to be a lot cheaper.All in all, and considering that I paid 60 Euros per night for this place I think it was one of the best value places I've been at. Excellent location and good accomodation. Recommended but bring earplugs if you are light sleeper. 
